 * Today's schedule: The section's 15 best teams will tee off at 8 a.m. at 
Canyon Country Club in Palm Springs. 
</P>
<P>
 * Defending champion: Palm Desert. 
</P>
<P>
 * Outlook: Although Palm Desert's 56-dual match winning streak was broken by 
Santa Barbara San Marcos this season, the two-time defending champion Aztecs 
are again the favorites. They won the Eastern Regional by two strokes over Palm 
Springs, despite playing poorly, according to Coach Tim Kabeary. The Aztecs won 
their first title in 1992 on this course. Westlake, which finished fourth last 
season and returns with largely the same team, won the Northern Regional by two 
shots over San Marcos. Loyola and Newhall Hart tied for first in the Western 
Regional. La Verne Damien won the Central Regional by two shots over Long Beach 
Millikan, and Dana Hills won the Southern Regional by three over Huntington 
Beach. MARTIN BECK 
