<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: FAVORITE PLACES; 
LONG BEACH DOG PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LESLIE CUMMINGS 
</P>
<P>
 Medical receptionist, Long Beach 
</P>
<P>
 "Finding the dog park was a godsend. Gaia loves it here. She's hyper and needs 
a big place to run.I can sit here and enjoy the sun. You see different dogs 
that you've never seen before. Also, if you like animals but can't have one 
it's a great place to come because you can play with the dogs." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The dog park was created after Clyde Cicotte received a $267 ticket for having 
his dog off-leash. He founded the Long Beach Dog Park Committee and the park 
opened last year. Cicotte says there have been some pet-owner romances as well 
as several marriages. "Pretty soon their dogs are in love and so are they," he 
says. 
</P>
<P>
 The dog park is located off 7th Street at Federation Drive in Recreation Park 
near the fly fishing casting pond. It is open from 6 a.m. to 10 p.m. daily.  
</P>
<P>
 Favorite Places columnist Jane Spiller welcomes suggestions for places that 
are publicly accessible and free. Contact her c/o Voices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
