</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On a day when former heavyweight champion Riddick Bowe was on hand, jockeys 
Brian Long and Antonio Castanon got into a scrap in front of the winner's 
circle after the 10th race at Hollywood Park on Sunday, continuing a battle 
that had begun during the stretch run. They were separated quickly with the 
help of trainer Sandy Shulman. 
</P>
<P>
 Long, riding longshot Vibrato Star, became upset after Castanon's mount, 
Someluckything, veered out sharply while tiring in midstretch. Someluckything 
interfered with Vibrato Star and others in the race, including eventual winner 
It's Settled. 
</P>
<P>
 A replacement for Eddie Delahoussaye, who didn't ride Sunday, Long appeared to 
start yelling at Castanon and swung at him with his whip after the incident and 
the two riders then started dueling with their whips on their way to the wire. 
</P>
<P>
 Both jockeys probably will be fined. BOB MIESZERSKI 
