<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAUGH LINES; TWO PICTURES WORTH 1,000 PUNCH LINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 So you think it's easy to write picture captions? 
</P>
<P>
 Laugh Lines' second reader-participation contest is writing captions for 
either or both of these two pictures. 
</P>
<P>
 Picture No. 1 is Los Angeles Mayor Richard Riordan, caught by cameras after a 
tennis tournament. No. 2 is Yasser Arafat talking to other dignitaries at the 
recent signing of a Middle East peace accord. 
</P>
<P>
 Below each picture is our sample of the kind of captions we are looking for in 
your entries. 
</P>
<P>
 So, put on your thinking caps and come up with something clever or creative. 
(We are not looking for a Top 10 list here, folks; just one or two funny gag 
lines for either or both photos.) 
</P>
<P>
 The top five captions for each picture will win a Laugh Lines Humor Master 
T-Shirt. The first-place winner for each picture -- as judged by the sometimes 
maligned LL Supreme Court -- will also receive an additional special prize. 
</P>
<P>
 Have some fun, and please make sure that we receive your entries by mail or 
fax no later than 9 a.m. Friday, May 20, 1994. 
</P>
