<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOP CARTOONISTS WIN SALUTE FROM PEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The National Cartoonist Society presented its 48th annual Reuben Awards in 
LaJolla Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Veteran comic-strip creators Charles Schulz ("Peanuts") and Mort Walker 
("Beetle Bailey") presented Jim Borgman of the Cincinnati Enquirer with the 
group's top honor, outstanding cartoonist of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Also honored were: Bud Grace ("Ernie"), in the newspaper comic strip division; 
Bill Rechin ("Out of Bounds"), newspaper panel; George Booth, gag cartoon; Bill 
Schorr (Kansas City Star), editorial cartoon; Drew Litton (Rocky Mountain 
News), sports cartoon; Mark Chiarello, comic book. 
</P>
<P>
 Other Reuben winners were Tim Burton, animation; Hal Mayforth, magazine and 
book illustration; Edward Sorel, advertising illustration; and W.B. Park, 
greeting card. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
