<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; PASTA DINNER OFFERED BEFORE TRIATHLON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reservations are being taken for the Carbo-Load Pasta Party on June 3, the 
night before the annual Mission Viejo triathlon. 
</P>
<P>
 The pasta party, sponsored by the Mission Viejo Cultural Arts Committee, will 
be from 5 to 10 p.m. at Norman P. Murray Community Center, 24932 Oso Viejo 
Road.  
</P>
<P>
 A complete pasta dinner, to be served from 6 to 8 p.m., costs $10 for adults, 
$5 for children 9 and younger. 
</P>
<P>
 For reservations, call Dru Cottrell, (714) 644-3150, or Hilda Baitoo, (714) 
768-8483. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations also can be made by sending a check to City Hall, 26522 La 
Alameda, Suite 190, Mission Viejo, Calif. 92691. Make the check out to the City 
of Mission Viejo.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
