<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; MEETING WEDNESDAY ON JUNE 7 ELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The June 7 election and its ballot issues will be discussed at a League of 
Women Voters meeting Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by the league's Capistrano Bay Area group, the meeting will be held 
at 7 p.m. at the California Federal Bank, 31872 Del Obispo St. 
</P>
<P>
 A panel will analyze the nine issues on the June ballot and respond to 
questions from the audience. 
</P>
<P>
 The League of Women Voters is a nonpartisan organization that encourages 
participation in government. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about Wednesday's meeting, call (714) 498-3956. For 
general questions about the League of Women Voters, call (714) 647-2343. FRANK 
MESSINA 
</P>
