<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; PROPOSAL WOULD HIKE WATER, SEWAGE RATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residential water and sewage rates in Ventura would rise 7% under a proposal 
the City Council will vote on tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 A median household in Ventura spends about $75.25 on water and sewage every 
two months.The ordinance under consideration would raise that bill by $4.91 
bimonthly. 
</P>
<P>
 The council voted 5 to 2 last week in preliminarily approving the increase, 
which also raises rates for commercial customers by 10% and industrial 
customers by 12% to 18%. Councilmen Jack Tingstrom and Jim Monahan voted 
against the increase because they said it was not good for business. 
</P>
<P>
 If approved, the increases would be effective July 1. 
</P>
<P>
 The fee hikes would pay for increased operating costs, and future water and 
sewer projects. A limited amount would pay for a low-interest loan program to 
help businesses invest in sanitation pre-treatment facilities that would lower 
their overall sanitation costs. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
