his lawyer said.Todd Maybrown said a hanging would likely decapitate Mitchell 
Rupe, who is sentenced to die for the 1981 murders of two bank tellers during a 
robbery. "Beheading was a punishment used in barbaric times," Maybrown said. 
"We don't accept bodily mutilation as a form of punishment now." No execution 
date has been set. State attorneys argue that the chance of decapitation is 
slight and, even if it does occur, won't necessarily inflict undue pain. 
</P>
