ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA HILLS; 4TH-GRADERS BRING HOME MATH HONORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A team of fourth-grade students from Valencia Elementary School took several 
awards during a recent countywide mathematics competition. 
</P>
<P>
 Competing against 23 other fourth-grade classes at the Orange County 
Mathematics Field Day held in Fountain Valley, the Valencia students won first 
place in mental math computation, along with second and third places in other 
categories. 
</P>
<P>
 The Valencia team, composed of Matthew Henry, Michelle Lee, Joanna Oster, Erik 
Sun and Jeffrey Kempler, studied for several months to prepare for the 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
